theorem
Th18: ((A in ( sigma_Field C ) & B in ( sigma_Field C )) implies ( A /\ B ) in ( sigma_Field C ))
proof
assume that
A1: A in ( sigma_Field C )
and
A2: B in ( sigma_Field C );
A3: ( X \ B ) in ( sigma_Field C ) by A2,CKB9:1;
( A /\ B ) c= ( X /\ X ) by A1,A2,XBOOLE_1:27;
then A4: ( A /\ B ) = ( X /\ ( A /\ B ) ) by XBOOLE_1:28
.= ( X \ ( X \ ( A /\ B ) ) ) by XBOOLE_1:48
.= ( X \ ( ( X \ A ) \/ ( X \ B ) ) ) by XBOOLE_1:54;
( X \ A ) in ( sigma_Field C ) by A1,CKB9:1;
then ( ( X \ A ) \/ ( X \ B ) ) in ( sigma_Field C ) by A3,CKB10:1;
hence thesis by A4,CKB9:1;
end;
